.nh
.TH "SYMAIRA" "1" "May 2026" "Symaira Vault" "OpenPass Manual"

.SH NAME
symaira-migrate-pseudonymize - Migrate vault entries to pseudonymized storage paths


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBsymaira migrate pseudonymize [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Migrate vault entries to pseudonymized storage paths.

.PP
WARNING: This rewrites every entry in the vault. Make a backup first.
Each entry is read, re-encrypted with its plaintext path stored inside
the encrypted data, and written to an HMAC-SHA256 derived path under
entries/. The old plaintext-named files are removed.

.PP
After migration, enable pseudonymize_paths in your vault config.yaml
to write new entries to pseudonymized paths.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for pseudonymize

.PP
\fB-y\fP, \fB--yes\fP[=false]
	Skip confirmation prompt


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--color\fP="auto"
	When to emit ANSI color: auto, always, never

.PP
\fB--no-pipe-warning\fP[=false]
	suppress 'reading from non-TTY' warning when piping secrets

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	Output format (text, json, yaml)

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	use a named vault profile

.PP
\fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	suppress non-error output

.PP
\fB--theme\fP=""
	Color preset: default, highcontrast, colorblind (or OPENPASS_THEME)

.PP
\fB--vault\fP="~/.openpass"
	path to the password vault


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  openpass migrate pseudonymize
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBsymaira-migrate(1)\fP
